column1: What the what? How are there no results?

Really? But isn't stuff like "where celebs went
to high school" easy to find online?

Usually yeah, but this time? No hits, even on
the underground sites.
All I'm seeing is fake info from deluded fans.

Even if she changed her name, there'd still
be traces of that somewhere, usually...
There's shit even YOU can't find, Futaba?

This reeks of a serious scrub job. Someone—
probably her—intentionally hid her past.

If we don't discover Alice's alma mater, we'll
never find a way into that secret room.

But, isn't it, like, impossible to just erase stuff
from the internet on your own?
Hmm, how else could we approach this?
What if Mako-chan's sister looks into it for us?

She's a prosecutor-turned-lawyer—maybe
she'll have access to useful intel we couldn't
gather ourselves.

Oh, that could work! Think it's doable,
Makoto?

I don't have a problem doing it, but how exactly
would I go about asking?

Personal information and histories are legally
protected, so I doubt she'd readily agree to
hand that over to us.

Yeah, just askin' her to tell us where Alice went
to school's not gonna fly...

I hear ya there. I really don't wanna wind up on
the other side of a table with her getting all,
"Answer me!"

I'm PubSec, not just some cop detect—
Wait, I'm not shady! Am I?

These kids are something else... Would you
quit sayin' that kinda stuff with that smile on
your face?

C'mon, enough with the cold shoulder.
You know I'm trying to help you out.

You wanna know where Alice Hiiragi went to
school, right?

Did you know how easy it was to eavesdrop
on you here?

But you can't find where that is—and that's
exactly how someone wants it.

Now there's an accurate description of PubSec
if I ever heard one.

For some reason, there's almost no personal
info available on Alice Hiiragi.

Especially prior to her debut—that is just a
big ol' blank.

So, since this is giving you all a hard time,
I've swooped in to lend a hand.

Intel on Alice would be no sweat for me over in
PubSec HQ, so how about it? Want some help?
Nah, we're good. We'll handle it on our own.

Yup, just a little more time and I'll get it
myself.
Great, happy to help— W-Wait, come on now!

This is a real-deal connection, here! Just
be grateful and take the intel!

We're sorry, we just have zero trust in the
police.
I told you to stop smilin' when you say that...

*sigh* Fine, I've gotta earn your trust first.
I get it.
Uhh, no. Everyone's senpai but yours.

And don't forget it—'cause you owe me one
now, got it?
It's hard to gauge whether he's friend or foe.

More importantly, how did he know where
Alice went to school?

Could the police already have their eyes on
her as well?
That we can trust him, for now at least.

Well, I guess all we can do now's try it...
We can find the secret room if we go to
Shujin, right?

That appears to be correct. Everything should
go SHOOWOWOWOWOW and we'll have access.

With that settled, let's all head to Shujin now.
There's no point in dawdling here.

Yeah, Makoto's right. Time to check out Shujin
Academy.
